eNCA's Monique Mortlock attended the Good Friday service at Saint George’s Cathedral in Cape Town.  CAPE TOWN - The last time Christians were able to observe Good Friday in the church was in 2019. This Easter weekend, throngs of believers will be able to celebrate in places of worship. Some church leaders say the festivities are marred by the government's COVID-19 safety regulation of A 50% cap on indoor venues. eNCA's Monique Mortlock attended the Good Friday service at Saint George’s Cathedral in Cape Town.